pageContext.claim: “Under the WTO, China is called a ‘developing nation.’ … We wrote them a letter and we said, much more strongly than the letter, that, not fair to have China as a developing nation. One of the reasons they've taken advantage of us is because of that. And we're considered the big, fat cow. And no longer. No longer.”
pageContext.analysis: Although it has become an economic powerhouse, China is not classified as a developed nation because wages and GDP per-capita remain relatively low.
